# Environment Variables Configuration
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values

# ==============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Comment System (Neon PostgreSQL)
# ==============================================================================
# The comment system is completely optional. If you don't want comments:
# 1. Simply don't set this variable
# 2. Remove or comment out the CommentsSection component from meditation posts
# 3. The site will work perfectly without it
#
# To enable comments:
# 1. Sign up for a free account at https://neon.tech
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Copy your connection string from the Neon dashboard
# 4. Paste it below (it should start with postgresql://)
# 5. Run the database initialization: POST to /api/comments/init
#
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/database?sslmode=require

# ==============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: Contact Form (Resend Email API)
# ==============================================================================
# The contact form is completely optional. If you don't want a contact form:
# 1. Simply don't set this variable
# 2. Remove the /contact page or replace it with alternative contact info
# 3. Update navigation to remove the contact link
#
# To enable the contact form:
# 1. Sign up for a free account at https://resend.com
# 2. Verify your domain (or use their test domain for development)
# 3. Create an API key in the Resend dashboard
# 4. Paste it below
# 5. Update the email addresses in app/api/contact/route.ts:
#    - Line ~32: from: 'Contact Form <contact@contact.yourdomain.com>'
#    - Line ~33: to: 'your.email@example.com'
#
# RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_api_key_here

# ==============================================================================
# Development vs Production
# ==============================================================================
# For local development:
# - Create .env.local and add your variables
# - .env.local is gitignored and won't be committed
#
# For production (Vercel):
# - Add environment variables in your Vercel project settings
# - Go to: Project Settings > Environment Variables
# - Add each variable individually
#
# Note: Never commit actual API keys or database credentials to git!
